<br>
Swimming under Freeport and trying to reach where ever the other side of the water was.  Of course, my swimming skill was about a 5 and I had no idea that PageUp/PageDown was an option.  I thought you just had to go for it.  I did.  It wasn't funny then.<br>
<br>
To make matters worse, when I got my corpse back, I went to the Rogue trainer in Freeport.  Hit autoattack instead of H for hail.  I learned how much riding a boat sucks.<br>
<br>
Last one:  This one wasn't me so it was really funny.  Me and two others decided to explore Luclin and we end up in Grimling Forest.  I decide to start jumping from the top of the hill above the rivermouth and into the river.  Eventually, the others did this while I took screenshots.  One of the guys was all excited about the screenshots, and jumped a bit to the side and SPLAT!!  I have a screenshot of it on my guild's webpage.  THAT was the best!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unimmbull.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nimmbull</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 9:24:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22777.topic&index=97>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dying</span><hr size=1> Taking my HP rings off to Bind wounds past 50%, and not having more than the 130 HPs I needed.  Yep, I've had a lot of dumb ones but that one still stings.  :P<br>
